## 🚫 NEVER DO THIS
- Don't use `var` (use `const` or `let`)
- Don't mutate state directly (use setState/reducer)
- Don't use class components (use functional components)
- Don't use `index.js` for components (use explicit names: `ComponentName.js`)
- Don't commit sensitive data (API keys, credentials)
- Don't skip error handling for async operations
- Don't write implementation before tests (follow TDG)
- Don't use real Firebase in tests (always mock)
- Don't ignore ESLint warnings (fix them)

---

## ✅ ALWAYS DO THIS
- Use `const` by default
- Use arrow functions for callbacks
- Use destructuring for props and imports
- Use `"use client"` directive when using React hooks in App Router
- Clean up Firebase listeners in `useEffect` returns
- Mock all external dependencies in tests
- Write tests before implementation (TDG)
- Use path alias `@/` for imports
- Handle loading and error states in components
- Use Firestore security rules for authorization

---

## 📚 SPLIT-ROUTING FOR KNOWLEDGE CAPTURE
When creating `.mdc` files in `.cursor/rules/`, always include:
- **Frontmatter**: `description:` and `globs:` fields
- **Topic-Specific Patterns**: Concrete examples from this project
- **Common Pitfalls**: Things to avoid based on our experience

Example `.mdc` structure:
```markdown
---
description: Standards for Firebase Firestore Integration
globs: **/firebase.js, **/lib/**.js
---
# FIRESTORE PATTERNS
- Always use `onSnapshot` for real-time updates
- Clean up listeners in `useEffect` return
- Use `serverTimestamp()` for timestamp fields
...
```
